{
  "message": "test(fixtures): force-add gitignored .db/.db-wal files required by CI\n\nTwo tests in tests/bench_cold_warm\n(test_isolated_workspace_failure_fixture_preserves_custom_metadata_targets\nand ..._preserves_sidecars_and_recovery_debris) assert on specific\nfiles inside tests/fixtures/workspace_failures/*/beads/.  Those files\n(custom.db, beads.db, beads.db-wal) match the `*.db` and `*.db-wal`\nrules in each fixture's local .gitignore, which mirrors a real\n.beads/ gitignore for fidelity.  As a result the files existed on\ndeveloper machines but were never pushed to git, so CI ran these\ntests on empty fixture directories and they failed with panics like\n\"custom database path should be preserved\".\n\nForce-add the five specific files the fixtures need (git add -f):\n- metadata_custom_paths/beads/custom.db     (healthy SQLite, 228K)\n- sidecar_wal_without_shm/beads/beads.db    (healthy SQLite, 228K)\n- sidecar_wal_without_shm/beads/beads.db-wal (stray WAL, 42 bytes)\n- interrupted_rebuild_leftovers/beads/beads.db     (ASCII \"bad\n  replacement database\", 58 bytes \u2014 this one is intentionally not\n  a valid SQLite file, per the fixture's failure story)\n- interrupted_rebuild_leftovers/beads/beads.db-wal (leftover WAL, 636K)\n\nThe fixture .gitignore files are left alone so future generated\n.db/.db-wal artifacts in these directories stay untracked \u2014 only\nthese five baseline fixture files are pinned in git.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
